RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 14 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 14 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONIQUES DAREDEVIL was allowed to settle in stride early, moved up three-wide nearing the quarter pole, took the lead leaving the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. DIXIELAND DANCER prompted Yeguita Queen from along the outside, responded during the drive and continued on well for the place. YEGUITA QUEEN opened clear early, then saved ground setting the pace into the stretch and weakened after being headed leaving the eighth pole. DANCIN DEE was reserved off the early pace, ranged up four-wide to offer a bid nearing the quarter pole and then flattened out during the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Yeguita Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear early, set pace inside, weakened drive

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 14. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOUD N PROUD saved ground setting the pace, lost the lead to Last Promise nearing the quarter pole, then responded gamely when put to pressure during the drive and edged clear late. LAST PROMISE was reserved off the early pace, moved up four-wide nearing the half mile pole to prompt the issue, gained the lead nearing the quarter pole but was unable to match strides with the winner late. ENGLISH LAUGHTER stalked the pace while racing three-wide, but was unable to reach the top two during the drive. ZONIC vied for the early lead from along the inside, dropped back before going a half mile and then improved his position during the drive. HONDO GUSTO was prominently placed for six furlongs and gave way. SHAKEM N BREAKEM was forwardly placed early from between horses and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Zonic
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early, saved ground, improved position late

ENTRY.NAME: Loud N Proud
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, responded, clear late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 14. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR. ANN prompted the pace set by Lyrical while racing along the outside, took the lead entering the stretch and gradually drew clear. JLO CAN DANCE saved ground while being unhurried, angled out three-wide entering the stretch and finished strongly for the place. LYRICAL saved ground setting the pace to the stretch, responded when headed and held on well for the show. EAST WING was fractious in the gate, then hit the side of the gate at the start, raced four-wide after that and failed to seriously threaten. CELESTIAL ORB was prominently placed into the stretch while racing three-wide and tired. ARETE'S CHALICE broke in the air to get away behind her field and failed to be a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Jlo Can Dance
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, saved ground, angled out stretch, strong finish

ENTRY.NAME: East Wing
ENTRY.OWNER: Lambholm Stable Felcher Ella and Preferred Pals Stable
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate, hit gate start, 4-wide trip, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Lyrical
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, held show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 90. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since March 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 14 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BORGOBYTHESEA saved ground setting the pace and maintained a safe advantage. FLY FLY AWAY was forwardly placed while racing two-wide and responded gamely during the drive to hold the place. JOE PHILLIPS was unhurried early, moved up four-wide to reach contention before going a half mile, offered a bid nearing the eighth pole but was unable to sustain his rally. LORD BARNA saved ground while being unhurried early, slipped through along the inside during the drive and gained his best stride too late. PRINCE AMADEUS weas allowed to settle in stride while racing between horses early but lacked the needed response when called upon. UNLEVERAGED saved ground while being forwardly placed to the stretch and weakened. SPETTACOLI (ARG) dropped backed early while racing three-wide and was not a serious factor. CHAOS KID prompted the early pace while racing three-wide and tired during the drive. CANDY COVE was three-wide early, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Borgobythesea
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, held advantage

ENTRY.NAME: Prince Amadeus
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, between horses, lacked needed response

ENTRY.NAME: Joe Phillips
ENTRY.OWNER: Jett North LLC Raven Kerri Asmus Annette and Asmus David

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $32,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since Mar ch 14 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 14 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R FUNNY BIZNESS saved ground while being reserved off the early pace, angled out 4-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished strongly to be up in the final sixteenth. BASKING stalked the pace while racing three-wide, moved up to offer a bid nearing the eighth pole, gained a slight lead between calls in the stretch but was unable to resist the winner late. LI'L MISS CAMILLE vied with Pink Shoelaces for the lead from along the inside, shook that one off entering the stretch, was unable to resist the top two but continued on well for the show. ADIOS BABY was allowed to settle in stride early, came five-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. PINK SHOELACES dueled for the lead from the outside to the stretch and tired. SHE'S MY WARRIOR was off a step slow, then showed some early speed and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: She's My Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: Mattson Peter D and Padilla Tim P
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow, early speed, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Li'l Miss Camille
ENTRY.OWNER: Winning Stables Inc and Averill Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Basking
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3-wide, bid 1/8, led between calls, caught late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOBLE FISH stalked the pace while racing three-wide, moved up to take the lead nearing the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. DUKE OF GLOUCESTER vided for the early lead with Sir Robert Hall from along the inside, shook that one off leaving the quarter pole, was no match for the winner but continued on well for the place. BOLD ADVANCE saved ground while being allowed to settle in stride, slipped through during the drive and improved his position. SIR ROBERT HALL dueled with Duke of Gloucester for the lead to the stretch and tired. SAGA was off a step slow and failed to meance. EXPANSIVE dropped well back early and showed little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1 1/16M Turf CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINELLA saved ground setting the pace and was ridden out to increase his advantage. BIALYSTOCK chased the pace from the outset, came two-wide into the stretch, could not reach the winner but finished well for second in a solid effort. STREET COP OFFICER broke in at the start then bobbled off horse's heels early, saved ground from that point and gradually improved his position. ONCE UPON A DREAM was unhurried early, rallied four-wide and was gaining slightly late. AWESOME HONOR was carried out on the first turn by Instigating, then settled in the middle of the field and failed to threaten. FOREVER SAUCY hopped slightly at the start, then moved up between horses on the turn, checked and stumbled entering the backstretch and was unable to recover. COLPO D'ORO was carried out on the first turn by Instigating, then was forwardly placed from between horses for six furlongs and tired. INSTIGATING ducked out causing interference on the first turn then moved up to force the issue for a half mile and gave way. DISCREET MAGIC was prominently placed early, moved up three-wide to offer a bid entering the stretch, ducked out leaving the eighth pole unseating his rider and continuing out to hit the rail. Following the race, Discreet Magic was unsaddled and walked off. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED INQUIRIES INTO THE FIRST TURN, THE INCIDENT ENERING THE BACKSTRETCH AND ALSO THE INCIDENT IN THE STRETCH, BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS, MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Minella
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, in hand late

ENTRY.NAME: Discreet Magic
ENTRY.COMMENT: prominent, 3-wide bid entering, ducked out 1/8, lost rider

ENTRY.NAME: Street Cop Officer
ENTRY.OWNER: Bruhns Erik Hudspath Jason Ross Randy and Ross Elizabeth Rose
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bobbled early, saved ground, improved position

ENTRY.NAME: Colpo d'Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: carried out 1st turn, forwardly placed 2-wide, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Instigating
ENTRY.COMMENT: ducked out 1st turn, prompted pace outside, gave way after 1/2

ENTRY.NAME: Forever Saucy
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, checked entering backstretch, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Honor
ENTRY.COMMENT: carried out 1st turn, mid pack, no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SISTER SAINT set the pressured pace while racing three-wide, responded when challenged by Shut It Cali and proved narrowly best in a prolonged drive. SHUT IT CALI was forwardly placed early while racing four-wide, moved up to engage Sister Saint nearing the quarter pole, dueled with that one to the wire and just missed in a game effort. UNCAPTURED DREAMS was allowed to settle in stride, moved up five-wide nearing the quarter pole to offer a bid and then went evenly late. BELLA'S CUPID was unhurried early, rallied six-wide the final quarter and gradually improved her position. ASHES TO ASHES was off a step slow and failed to threaten while raciing two-wide. MISS NEO was fractious in the gate, then vied for the early lead from between horses and weakened. MO TOWN ANNIE was not a factor while saving ground. RED DELICIOUS dueled for the early lead from along the inside for a half mile and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Sister Saint
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, 3-wide, best, prolonged drive

ENTRY.NAME: Shut It Cali
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed 4-wide, bold bid 1/4, just missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1 1/16M Turf CR: 88. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 14 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Consid ered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOURBON BLAST was allowed to settle in stride, rallied four-wide nearing the quarter pole, took the lead entering the stretch and gradually edged clear. COOL FRONT was reserved off the early pace, moved up five-wide on the turn and finished strongly. SNEAKY CHEEKY was unhurried early, moved up three-wide on the turn and finished in a mild rally. CLASSY OF COURSE was forwardly placed from the start and went evenly. PURE ELEGANCE was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and failed to menace. ONE NIGHT STAND dropped back early, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to seriously threaten. LIZZ A BEE raced three-wide and failed to menace. DIA DE SOL dueled for the lead from along the outside and tired. TIMELESS GLORY vied for the early lead from along the inside and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Bourbon Blast
